WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.500
Here is ReplyPilot. Let’s follow one real support question from the moment it arrives.

00:00:06.500 --> 00:00:13.000
The customer shares their contact details, order number, and what went wrong.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:23.000
ReplyPilot identifies the category, urgency, and sentiment, then searches the company knowledge base.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:31.000
It prepares a professional response and shows the sources it used—but nothing is sent automatically.

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:41.000
A human can review every word, make changes, reject the draft, or generate another version.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:49.000
Only approval unlocks the send action.

00:00:49.000 --> 00:01:00.000
The approved email is delivered, and every step stays visible in the support dashboard.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:09.000
That means faster responses, consistent answers, and full control over every customer conversation.

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:18.000
I’m John Venancio, an AI Automation Developer. Try the live demo, or contact me.
